cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it deals with the role of individual layers in deep neural networks and the transferable properties of the data representations they learn. It also proposes a novel correspondence between Gaussian Processes and SGD trained deep neural networks, which is a common technique used in machine learning. 

The paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category as it deals with the optimization of deep neural networks and the understanding of their internal representations, which are important topics in AI research. 

The cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category is also a possibility as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. 

The cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category is relevant as the paper deals with deep neural networks and their optimization, which are topics within the scope of neural computing. 

Finally, the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with the optimization of deep neural networks, which can be seen as a control problem.
